      "title": "Respiratory History",
      "fields": [
        { "type": "note", "tone": "ayurveda", "content": "🌿 Tamaka Shwasa (Bronchial Asthma) is the most common Pranavaha Srotas Roga. It is predominantly Vata-Kapha with Kapha obstruction in Pranavaha Srotas. Key Ayurveda distinction: Tamaka Shwasa is worse in Vasanta + Hemanta (Kapha seasons) and on cold exposure. Vamana is the primary Shodhana; Nasya + Dhoomapana are supplementary." },
        { "type": "note", "tone": "warning", "content": "⚠ Danger signs requiring emergency: SpO₂ <90%; RR >30/min; unable to complete sentences; pulsus paradoxus; silent chest on auscultation (no wheeze = total obstruction). These are life-threatening — IV bronchodilators + O₂ first." },
